Fig. 8b represents the EIS curves of PCO and COC. The prevalence of the gradient can be credited to the diffusion of charges along the electrode surface, asserting the PSC or battery-type trait of the electrodes. The first point of convergence of the semicircle and X-axis gives the magnitude of solution resistance (Rs
) and the diameter of the semicircle denotes the value of charge transfer resistance (Rct
). The parameters of the Nyquist graph calculated using a fitted equivalent circuit (Fig. 8c) are illustrated in Table 1
. In the high-frequency region, COC displays a lower charge transfer resistance than PCO, suggesting fast ion and electron mobility in the case of COC electrode.
